Beyond photoaging: additional factors involved in the process of skin aging.

Addor FAS(1).

Author information:
(1)MEDCIN Research, Private Clinical Research Center, Osasco, São Paulo, Brazil, 
flavia.addor@medcin.com.br.

Studies assessing the impact of extrinsic factors on skin aging have increased 
during the last with the increase in life expectancy. Although most of the 
studies are about the sun radiation impact, many factors should be considered in 
elderly people, beyond environmental conditions. Lifestyle factors, like diet, 
sleeping, smoking, should be analyzed carefully, as common age-related 
conditions (menopause, diabetes, pulmonary diseases, etc.). All these factors 
could accelerate the natural decline of skin structure and functions, possibly 
affecting the responses to treatments and drugs. This review demonstrates that 
growing evidence regarding environmental factors that are associated with 
lifestyle and comorbidities deserve greater attention from researchers and 
dermatologists and may require new approaches in the management of skin aging.

